text: Ukiah ( ; formerly Ukiah City) is the county seat and largest city of Mendocino County, California. The Ukiah Valley is a center of a major wine production industry.Palmer, 'History of Mendocino County, California, pg. 476. The population was 16,607 at the 2020 census. ==References== Category:Cities in California Category:County seats in California Category:Settlements in Mendocino County, California
title: Ukiah, California
